cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.LG 

This paper deals with natural language processing and semantic web technologies, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on linguistic analysis and translation of Arabic queries suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The use of SPARQL and ontology-based knowledge bases suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) as other possible sub-categories. The use of machine learning and semantic features suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as additional possibilities.
